About Us - Bamford History Group Log in Menu Home About Us History of Bamford Our Buildings Bamford School Lost Villages Our Archive Useful Links Classified Ads Search Go About Us Home About Us The History Group was formed several years ago to study, preserve and share the history of Bamford and the surrounding areas including Bamford, Thornhill, Derwent, Ashopton and Hope Woodlands. We hold monthly meetings, usually on the second Friday night in the month, depending on the availability of speakers and we also arrange visits to places of interest in the summer. We arrange exhibitions, events and visits to places of interest. We study the history of our area through projects and activities. We preserve and collect local records and documents. We are a friendly group and welcome new members.Â  Our meetings are open to Institute Members and Non-Members.Â  If you are interested in any aspect of local history research do get in touch at bamfordhistorygroup@outlook.com Committee Members Kathleen Greenan (Chair and Secretary) Robert Helliwell (Treasurer) Committee members: Jennifer Fox, Sarah Helliwell, Janet Skirrow. We are one of the User Groups of Bamford Institute. Members of the Institute are automatically members of the History Group. You can join the Institute at any of our meetings or e mail us to find out more. Voice Online Communities - Leave Feedback - Terms - Privacy - Cookies

Google Maps Cobalt Square 11th Floor, 83-85 Hagley Road, Birmingham, B16 8QG info@sportbirmingham.org 0121 296 5190 Get directions By train The nearest train station is Fiveways. This can be reached from New Street station depending on which area of the West Midlands you are coming from. When leaving the station, take a left and walk up towards Five Ways Roundabout, (you can walk under the roundabout walkway and up onto Hagley Road). Cobalt Square is the blue office block across the road from Morrisons, and next to Tricorn House. This will take approx. 10 minutes. By bus From the city centre (Grand Central) take the 80/80A on Smallbrook Queensway outside the bullring to Frederick Road (5 stops). Once off the bus walk under Fiveways roundabout exiting at the first underpass on your left. This will bring you out next to Morrisons. Cobalt Square is directly opposite. By bike There are multiple ways to reach our offices on bike from city centre. For example via Broad street, on site we have bike racks situated at the back of the car park on ground floor. By car Hagley Road â€“ If coming from the Hagley Road towards Fiveways roundabout, before reaching the roundabout you will see Cobalt Square (blue offices) on the left and Morrisons on the right-hand side. Continue to the roundabout and take first exit towards Ladywood Middleway where you can park in Broadway Plaza. Parking: There are a number of car parking options, however, we recommend using Broadway Plaza which can be accessed via Fiveways Roundabout. From the roundabout head down Ladywood Middleway and parking entrance is on the left hand side. It will cost between Â£2-5 depending on length of stay. You can also park at Morrisons FREE for 2hours if you purchase something in store. Welcome to Bamford Fieldhouse Cricket Club - About Us Home Room Hire Menu ï€ Home The Club About Us Function Room Hire Juniors Join Our Juniors The Club has a strong junior section with boys and girls enjoying learning to play cricket in a friendly and safe environment.
			                    		â€¦ More Junior Section Junior Registrations Fixtures Training Contact Us Room Hire News Contact About Bamford Fieldhouse Cricket Club Bamford Fieldhouse Cricket Club is a popular cricket and sports club based in Rochdale. Founded in 1850 and then called only "Fieldhouse" , the club was originally located at John Bright's Fieldhouse Mill off Whitworth Road in Rochdale. In 1895 the club played competitive cricket in what was then known as the South East Lancashire League and after a break for the first world war the club began playing competitive cricket again in 1921 in the South Lancashire cricket league where it remained until 1994 From left to right: The original "fieldhouse" gate that the players still walk through to take to the field, the fire damaged clubhouse, the beautiful outside terrace area and finally the stunning view of ground and clubhouse In 1982 the club relocated to its current home on Hollin Lane in Bamford Rochdale, where it is still situated today. In 1994 the club joined the Saddleworth and District Cricket League and at the same time additional investment was made into the club infrastructure. The last ten years of competitive matches in this league brought with it over seven regional cup winners' trophies and six first division championships combined with many trophies for the juniors. In September 2008 the club received a major setback when, despite the best attempts of four teams of firefighters, the club was ravaged by fire after an arson attack and the club yet again had to begin the process of not only rebuilding the clubhouse but also trying to find the revenues to replace those that were lost through the lack of events through 2008 and 2009. Despite this huge setback the process of rebuilding began and since then the club has never looked back. It now boasts argueably the best cricket facilities and function room in the locality. The club is particularly proud of its junior teams and coaching sessions with under 9s, 11s, and 13s, with an under 15s side also planned for next year.The development of our junior section is at the very heart of what the club looks to achieve.

				  Our objectives are clear Ã¢Â€Â“ we want to foster a happy, safe and unpressurised environment where children can develop a love for the game that they can take through life and along the way, produce the next generation of cricketers. The club has SKY TV, shows live football, cricket and major sporting events and is the perfect place to enjoy a drink in a cosy relaxed atmosphere Our clubhouse is available for hire to the local community and we believe it is an ideal venue to host your private function. Whether it be a Birthday or Special Occasion that you are having, our function room is perfect.It has a capacity of 150+ people and there is a fully licensed bar. Being a sports and social club our drink prices are very reasonable and we will also try our best to cater for any special requests that you may have, just make sure you let us know in advance. If you are interested in booking our clubhouse for hire then click here. "Despite this huge setback the process of rebuilding the club began and since that time the club has never looked back, it now boasts arguably the best cricket facilities and function room in the locality".
